results.name: Sum of largest parts of all partitions of n into odd distinct parts.
reference: Knopfmacher, Arnold and Robbins, Neville, Identities for the total number of parts in partitions of integers. Util. Math. 67 (2005), 9-18.
mathematica: nmax = 50; Rest[CoefficientList[Series[Sum[(2*k - 1)*x^(2*k - 1) * Product[1 + x^(2*j - 1), {j, 1, k - 1}], {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x]] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jun 28 2016 *)
